Regression Title
Different results for the same intent with alternate phrasing

Environment
- ENVIRONMENT: PREPROD
- COUNTRY: AU
- PRODUCT: NCOS
- LANGUAGE: en

Problem Summary
Different results are returned even though the user intent is the same.

Observed Queries
Q1: white car for families
Observed result:
- Only EQA came out

Q2: white family cars
Observed result:
- More vehicle options were returned

Expected Behaviour
- Results should be consistent across related phrasings with the same intent.
- Vehicle recommendations should not narrow unexpectedly for equivalent wording.
- If filters are applied, they should stay aligned with the intent: family cars + white color.

Validation Scope
- Include wording variations for the same intent.
- Include synonyms such as family car, family vehicle, car for families.
- Include nearby phrasing changes such as white family SUV, family-friendly white car.
- Check both recommendation quality and applied filters.

Notes
- Focus on semantic consistency rather than exact wording.
- Add RCA and test approach below this line after AI analysis if needed.